Step 1. Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• Formula: Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
• Accounts Receivable at beginning = 0.00, at end = 1,133,414.13  
• Average Accounts Receivable = (0.00 + 1,133,414.13) / 2 = 566,707.065  
• Main Business Revenue = 5,991,764.34  
• Turnover Ratio = 5,991,764.34 / 566,707.065 ≈ 10.57  

Step 2. Operating Cash Flow Ratio and Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• Both ratios are computed as: Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Current Liabilities  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 215,423.24  
• Total Current Liabilities = 1,124,588.25  
• Ratio = 215,423.24 / 1,124,588.25 ≈ 0.1917, which rounds to 0.19  

Step 3. Total Asset Turnover Ratio  
• Formula: Revenue / Average Total Assets  
• Total Assets at beginning = 13,000,000.00, at end = 15,288,131.32  
• Average Total Assets = (13,000,000.00 + 15,288,131.32) / 2 = 14,144,065.66  
• Ratio = 5,991,764.34 / 14,144,065.66 ≈ 0.4235, which rounds to 0.42  

Step 4. Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Formula: Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity  
• Total Liabilities (current liabilities) = 1,124,588.25  
• Total Owner's Equity (end) = 14,163,543.07  
• Ratio = 1,124,588.25 / 14,163,543.07 ≈ 0.0794, which rounds to 0.08  

Thus, the results are:

{
  "solution": {
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "10.57",
    "operating cash flow ratio": "0.19",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "0.19",
    "Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.42",
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.08"
  }
}
